Alexis Douglas was playing at her sister's friend's house in Melbourne when a neighbour's pitbull attacked her face  . 
  The five-year-old needed 50 stitches to her face and requires treatment for the next three years . 
  Her mother Monique Douglas says she cries every day for her daughter . 
  The dog owner Edward Powell was handed a $1500 fine and no convictions for not registering his pitbull . 
  Alexis was left with deep gashes of up to 10cm . 
  She was mauled by the dog a week after her fifth birthday . 
 